crosses (with strategy)

Checks if two geometries crosses.

Synopsis 

template<typename Geometry1, typename Geometry2, typename Strategy>
bool crosses(Geometry1 const & geometry1, Geometry2 const & geometry2, Strategy const & strategy)

Parameters

Type

Concept

Name

Description

Geometry1 const &

Any type fulfilling a Geometry Concept

geometry1

A model of the specified concept

Geometry2 const &

Any type fulfilling a Geometry Concept

geometry2

A model of the specified concept

Strategy const &

Any type fulfilling a Crosses Strategy Concept

strategy

The strategy which will be used for crosses calculations

Returns

Returns true if two geometries crosses

Header

Either

#include <boost/geometry.hpp>

Or

#include <boost/geometry/algorithms/crosses.hpp>

Conformance

The function crosses implements function Crosses from the OGC Simple Feature Specification.

Supported geometries

Point

Segment

Box

Linestring

Ring

Polygon

MultiPoint

MultiLinestring
